{
  "texts": [
    "For example, Tesla faced several class action lawsuits alleging deceptive marketing of its driving assistance systems as autonomous driving technology, using names like \"Autopilot\" and \"Full Self-Driving Capability.\"",
    "82 The plaintiffs claim that Tesla used these terms despite knowing the autonomous driving claims were misleading.",
    "83 Studies have shown that terms like \"Autopilot\" can lead to driver misinterpretations.",
    "84 Product liability and regulatory standards can ensure that producers market their (semi-)autonomous products responsibly.",
    "In 2022, the UK proposed a rule holding manufacturers liable for the actions of self-driving vehicles when they are operating in autonomous mode."
  ]
}